15|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120201106/http://www.incademy.com/courses/ten-great-investors/-warren-buffett/1/1040/10002|archivedate=November 20, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Farrington|first1=Robert|title=The top 10 investors of all time|url=http://thecollegeinvestor.com/972/the-top-10-investors-of-all-time|website=The College Investor|publisher=The College Investor, LLC|accessdate=November 20, 2015|date=April 22, 2011}}</ref> and has a [[net worth]] of [[US$]]88.9&nbsp;billion as of December 2019, making him the [[The World's Billionaires|fourth-wealthiest person in the world]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Warren Buffett|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/warren-buffett|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref>Was raised as a [[Presbyterian]], but has since described himself as [[agnostic]].<ref>[https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/14.11/faces3.html ''Wired''] article ''Faces of the New Atheism: The Scribe'' published November 2006. Retrieved November 10, 2009.</ref>\n|-\n|[[Bart Campolo]]<ref name=\"NYT\">{{cite web|last1=Oppenheimer|first1=Mark|title=The Evangelical Scion Who Stopped Believing|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/29/magazine/the-evangelical-scion-who-stopped-believing.html|website=The New York Times|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=5 July 2017|date=29 Dec 2016}}</ref>\n|[[United States]]\n|Humanist chaplain and son of pastor [[Tony Campolo]].\n|-\n|[[Fidel Castro]]\n|[[Cuba]]\n|Cuban communist revolutionary and politician; Prime Minister of Cuba (1959\u20131976), and President (1976\u20132008); [[Baptism|baptized]] into the Roman Catholic Church at the age of eight; later became an atheist.<ref>{{harvnb|Bourne|1986|pp=29\u201330}}; {{harvnb|Coltman|2003|pp=5\u20136}}; {{harvnb|Castro and Ramonet|2009|pp=59\u201360}}.</ref>\n|-\n|[[Nikolay&nbsp;Chernyshevsky]]<ref>[Ana Siljak, Angel of Vengeance, page 58]</ref>\n|[[Russia]]\n|Revolutionary democrat, materialist philosopher, critic, and socialist.\n|-\n|[[Winston Churchill]]\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|Prime Minister; christened in the [[Church of England]],{{sfn|Reagles|Larsen|2013|p=8}} converted to agnosticism.{{sfnm|1a1=Haffner|1y=2003|1p=32|2a1=Reagles|2a2=Larsen|2y=2013|2p=8}}\n|-\n|[[Helen Clark]]\n|[[New Zealand]]\n|Prime Minister; raised Presbyterian, converted to agnosticism.<ref name=\"religion\">{{cite news |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/section/story.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=3554978 |first=Audrey |last=Young |newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |date=16 March 2004 |title=Insults get personal between Clark and Brash |accessdate=8 July 2007 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6872spJCK?url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=3554978 |archivedate=2 June 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Pat Condell]]\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|Writer, political commentator, comedian and atheist [[Viral videos#Internet celebrities|internet personality]].<ref name=\"time-out-london\">{{cite web |last=Hay |first=Malcolm |title=Pat Condell: interview |publisher=Time Out London |date=3 November 2006 |url=https://www.timeout.com/london/comedy/features/2217/Pat_Condell-interview.html |accessdate=20 August 2010|quote=Condell\u2019s 56. He was born an Irish Catholic but educated in Church of England schools.}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Charles Darwin]]<ref name=Belief>{{cite web|url=http://www.darwinproject.ac.uk/content/view/130/125/|title=Darwin Correspondence Project&nbsp;\u2013 Belief: historical essay|accessdate=25 November 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090225124103/http://www.darwinproject.ac.uk/content/view/130/125/ |archivedate=25 February 2009 }}</ref><ref name=Fordyce>[http://www.darwinproject.ac.uk/darwinletters/calendar/entry-12041.html Letter 12041]&nbsp;\u2013 Darwin, C. R. to Fordyce, John, 7 May 1879</ref>\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|British naturalist, geologist and biologist, best known for his contributions to the science of evolution; raised as a Unitarian, later became an agnostic.\n|-\n|[[Richard Dawkins]]\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|British ethologist, evolutionary biologist and author; was brought up as an Anglican until ceasing to believe in a deity in his teens, concluding that the theory of evolution was a better explanation for life's complexity.\n|-\n|[[Jerry DeWitt]]\n|[[United States]]\n|Former pastor of two evangelical churches; publicly converted to [[atheism]] in 2011 after twenty-five years of Christian ministry.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jerry DeWitt|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jerry-dewitt/|publisher=Huffington Post|accessdate=19 January 2014}}</ref> He has written a book based on his career and experiences entitled ''Hope After Faith''.<ref name=Telegram>{{cite web|last=McKeon|first=Melissa|title=Former evangelist-turned-atheist to speak April 9 at UU Church|url=http://www.telegram.com/article/20130329/TOWNNEWS/303299996&TEMPLATE=TOWNPORTAL|publisher=Telegram|date=March 29, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Matt Dillahunty]]\n|[[United States]]\n|Public speaker, raised Southern Baptist, considered becoming a minister. His religious studies, instead of bolstering his faith as he intended, led him to no longer believe in Christianity and then all religions.\n|-\n|nowrap|[[Jonathan Edwards (triple jumper)|Jonathan Edwards]]<ref>[http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/sport/more_sport/athletics/article1991114.ece?Submitted=true The Times]</ref>\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|Former British triple jumper; former Olympic, Commonwealth, European and World champion; formerly a devout Christian, and even presented episodes of the BBC Christian worship programme ''Songs of Praise.''\n|-\n|[[Ricky Gervais]]\n|[[United Kingdom]]\n|Actor, abandoned Christianity at the age of eight.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/factual/desertislanddiscs_20070624.shtml|title=BBC Radio 4 \u2013 Factual&nbsp;\u2014 Desert Island Discs&nbsp;\u2014 Ricky Gervais}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Julia Gillard]]\n|[[Australia]]\n|Prime Minister; brought up in the Baptist faith, 