39 |accessdate=10 December 2005 |language=Polish |ref=harv |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050927194547/http://encyklopedia.pwn.pl/33490_1.html |archivedate=27 September 2005 }}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book |first=Jochen |last=B\u00f6hler |title=Auftakt zum Vernichtungskrieg; Die Wehrmacht in Polen 1939 (Preface to the War of Annihilation: Wehrmacht in Poland) |year=2006 |publisher=Fischer Taschenbuch Verlag |location=Frankfurt |isbn=978-3-596-16307-6 |language=German}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Jan T. Gross |last=Gross |first=Jan T. |title=Revolution from Abroad: The Soviet Conquest of Poland's Western Ukraine and Western Belorussia |location=Princeton |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-691-09603-2}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Forczyk |first1=Robert |title=Case White: The Invasion of Poland 1939 |date=2019 |publisher=Osprey Publishing |location=Oxford |isbn=978-1472834959}}\n* {{cite book | author-link= Roger Moorhouse | first= Roger | last= Moorhouse | title= First to Fight: The Polish War 1939 | year= 2019 | publisher= [[The Bodley Head]] |isbn=978-1847924605 }}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote|Polish September Campaign}}\n{{Commons category|Polish Defensive War of 1939}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Proclamation to the German Army (1 September 1939)}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Address to the Reichstag (1 September 1939)}}\n{{Wikisource|Communication from the German Government to the British Government in Response to Great Britain's Ultimatum (3 September 1939)}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Proclamation to the German People (3 September 1939)}}\n* [http://www1.yadvashem.org/yv/en/holocaust/about/02/occupation.asp?WT.mc_id=wiki The Conquest of Poland and the Beginnings of Jewish Persecution] on the [[Yad Vashem]] website\n* [http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/system/topicRoot/German_invasion_of_Poland/ German invasion of Poland] Original reports from The Times\n* [http://www.ibiblio.org/