cite book |authorlink=Richard C. Lukas |last=Lukas |first=Richard C. |title=Forgotten Holocaust: The Poles Under German Occupation, 1939\u20131944 |publisher=Hippocrene Books |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-7818-0901-6}}\n* {{cite book |last=Majer |first=Diemut |title=Non-Germans under the Third Reich: The Nazi Judicial and Administrative System in Germany and Occupied Eastern Europe, with Special Regard to Occupied Poland, 1939\u20131945 |publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press |year=2003 |isbn= 978-0-8018-6493-3|display-authors=et al.}}\n* {{cite press release |title=Nazi Loss in Poland Placed at 290,000 |work=The New York Times |date=28 September 1941 |url=https://select.nytimes.com/mem/archive/pdf?res=F50E11F63C5E1A7A93CAAB1782D85F458485F9 |accessdate=17 January 2009}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Anita J. Prazmowska |last=Prazmowska |first=Anita J. |title=Britain and Poland 1939\u20131943: The Betrayed Ally |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=1995 |isbn=978-0-521-48385-8}}\n* {{cite book |last=Piotrowski |first=Tadeusz |authorlink=Tadeusz Piotrowski (sociologist) |year=1998 |title=Poland's Holocaust: Ethnic Strife, Collaboration With Occupying Forces and Genocide in the Second Republic, 1918\u20131947 |location=Jefferson, NC |publisher=McFarland & Company |isbn=978-0-7864-2913-4 |ref=harv |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hC0-dk7vpM8C}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=George Sanford (scholar) |last=Sanford |first=George |year=2005 |title= Katyn and the Soviet Massacre of 1940: Truth, Justice And Memory |location=London, New York | publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-0-415-33873-8 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Seidner |first=Stanley S. |year=1978 |title=Marshal Edward \u015amig\u0142y-Rydz: Rydz and the Defence of Poland |location=New York}}\n* {{cite book |editor1-last=Taylor |editor1-first=A.J.P. |editor2-last=Mayer |editor2-first=S.L. |title=A History of World War Two |location=London |publisher=Octopus Books |year=1974 |isbn=978-0-7064-0399-2 |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofworldwa00tayl }}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Gerhard Weinberg |last=Weinberg |first=Gerhard |year=1994 |title=A World at Arms: A Global History of World War II |location=Cambridge |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-44317-3 |url=https://archive.org/details/worldatarmsgloba00wein }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Zaloga |first1=Steve |last2=Gerrard |first2=Howard |title=Poland 1939: The Birth of Blitzkrieg |location=Oxford |publisher=Osprey Publishing |year=2002 |isbn=978-1-84176-408-5}}\n* {{cite book |last=Zaloga |first=Steve |title=The Polish Army 1939\u20131945 |location=Oxford |publisher=Osprey Publishing |year=1982 |isbn=978-0-85045-417-8}}\n* {{cite encyclopedia |encyclopedia=[[Internetowa encyklopedia PWN]] |url=http://encyklopedia.pwn.pl/33490_1.html |title=KAMPANIA WRZE\u015aNIOWA 1939 |accessdate=10 December 2005 |language=Polish |ref=harv |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050927194547/http://encyklopedia.pwn.pl/33490_1.html |archivedate=27 September 2005 }}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{cite book |first=Jochen |last=B\u00f6hler |title=Auftakt zum Vernichtungskrieg; Die Wehrmacht in Polen 1939 (Preface to the War of Annihilation: Wehrmacht in Poland) |year=2006 |publisher=Fischer Taschenbuch Verlag |location=Frankfurt |isbn=978-3-596-16307-6 |language=German}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Jan T. Gross |last=Gross |first=Jan T. |title=Revolution from Abroad: The Soviet Conquest of Poland's Western Ukraine and Western Belorussia |location=Princeton |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-691-09603-2}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Forczyk |first1=Robert |title=Case White: The Invasion of Poland 1939 |date=2019 |publisher=Osprey Publishing |location=Oxford |isbn=978-1472834959}}\n* {{cite book | author-link= Roger Moorhouse | first= Roger | last= Moorhouse | title= First to Fight: The Polish War 1939 | year= 2019 | publisher= [[The Bodley Head]] |isbn=978-1847924605 }}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote|Polish September Campaign}}\n{{Commons category|Polish Defensive War of 1939}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Proclamation to the German Army (1 September 1939)}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Address to the Reichstag (1 September 1939)}}\n{{Wikisource|Communication from the German Government to the British Government in Response to Great Britain's Ultimatum (3 September 1939)}}\n{{Wikisource|Adolf Hitler's Proclamation to the German People (3 September 1939)}}\n* [http://www1.yadvashem.org/yv/en/holocaust/about/02/occupation.asp?WT.mc_id=wiki The Conquest of Poland and the Beginnings of Jewish Persecution] on the [[Yad Vashem]] website\n* [http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/system/topicRoot/German_invasion_of_Poland/ German invasion of Poland] Original reports from The Times\n* [http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USA/DAP-Poland/Campaign-III.html Detailed outline of campaign, mainly from German documents]\n* [http://ww2db.com/battle_spec.php?battle_id=28 The Campaign in Poland at WorldWar2 Database]\n* [http://www.achtungpanzer.com/polcamp.htm The Campaign in Poland at Achtung! Panzer]\n* [http://www.feldgrau.com/stats.html German Statistics including September Campaign losses]\n* [http://www.schoolshistory.org.uk/EuropeatWar/blitzkrieg_poland.htm Brief Campaign losses and more statistics]\n* [http://worldatwar.net/article/poland39/index.html Fall Wei\u00df \u2013 The Fall of Poland]\n* [http://www.history.com/video.do?name=militaryhistory&bcpid=1681694250&bclid=1699210677&bctid=1606750320 Radio reports on the German invasion of Poland]{{dead link|date=March 2020|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} and [http://www.history.com/video.do?name=militaryhistory&bcpid=1681694250&bclid=1699210677&bctid=1606750307 Nazi broadcast claiming that Germany's action is an act of defence]{{dead link|date=March 2020|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/september/1/newsid_3506000/3506335.stm Headline s